## Priority-bearing records

MX, SRV, and URI records must configure priority only within `data`. Do not set the top-level `priority` attribute: it is a read-only computed value that may be returned by the API and does not need to be duplicated in Terraform configuration.

MX records also configure their target within `data`:

```terraform
resource "cloudflare_dns_record" "mx" {
  zone_id = var.zone_id
  name    = "@"
  type    = "MX"
  ttl     = 300

  data = {
    priority = 10
    target   = "mail.example.com"
  }
}
```

SRV and URI records retain their existing structured fields and place priority alongside them in `data`.

